    "description": "Olof L. Danils was a Swedish agronom and director. He was born on January 22, 1873 in Malung, Kopparb. County, Sweden. He was the son of Danils Lars Halvarsson and Kerstin Jonsdotter. He married Elin Lindskog in 1907 and they had two children, Halvar and Gunnel. Olof L. Danils attended Örebro Technical Gymnasium, Alnarp Agricultural Institute, and Alnarp Dairy Institute. He also studied at the University of Halle and at the Dairy Institute in Hameln and Kilmarnock. He wrote a book about milking in 1903 and received the Patriotic Society's medal." 
